docs.lead_paragraph: The health of New Yorkers was "exceptionally good" in 1954. Dr. Leona Baumgartner, Commissioner of Health, announced yesterday The death rate was lower and the birth rate higher than in 1953.

headline.main: CITY'S HEALTH FINE IN 1954, THANK YOU; Birth Rate Higher and Death Rate Lower Than in 1953, Dr. Baumgartner Says
